name: NFCORE_RNASEQ:RNASEQ:PREPARE_GENOME:SALMON_INDEX (genome.transcripts.fa)
script:
grep '^>' genome.fa | cut -d ' ' -f 1 | cut -d $'\t' -f 1 > decoys.txt
sed -i.bak -e 's/>//g' decoys.txt
cat genome.transcripts.fa genome.fa > gentrome.fa

salmon \
    index \
    --threads 6 \
    -t gentrome.fa \
    -d decoys.txt \
     \
    -i salmon

cat <<-END_VERSIONS > versions.yml

name: NFCORE_RNASEQ:RNASEQ:ALIGN_STAR:STAR_ALIGN_IGENOMES (K562_REP1)
script:
STAR \
    --genomeDir STARIndex \
    --readFilesIn K562_REP1_1_val_1.fq.gz K562_REP1_2_val_2.fq.gz  \
    --runThreadN 12 \
    --outFileNamePrefix K562_REP1. \
     \
    --sjdbGTFfile genes.gtf \
    --outSAMattrRGline ID:K562_REP1 'SM:K562_REP1'   \
    --quantMode TranscriptomeSAM --twopassMode Basic --outSAMtype BAM Unsorted --readFilesCommand zcat --runRNGseed 0 --outFilterMultimapNmax 20 --alignSJDBoverhangMin 1 --outSAMattributes NH HI AS NM MD --quantTranscriptomeBan Singleend --outSAMstrandField intronMotif



if [ -f K562_REP1.Unmapped.out.mate1 ]; then
    mv K562_REP1.Unmapped.out.mate1 K562_REP1.unmapped_1.fastq
    gzip K562_REP1.unmapped_1.fastq
fi
if [ -f K562_REP1.Unmapped.out.mate2 ]; then
    mv K562_REP1.Unmapped.out.mate2 K562_REP1.unmapped_2.fastq
    gzip K562_REP1.unmapped_2.fastq
fi

cat <<-END_VERSIONS > versions.yml
"NFCORE_RNASEQ:RNASEQ:ALIGN_STAR:STAR_ALIGN_IGENOMES":
    star: $(STAR --version | sed -e "s/STAR_//g")
    samtools: $(echo $(samtools --version 2>&1) | sed 's/^.*samtools //; s/Using.*$//')
    gawk: $(echo $(gawk --version 2>&1) | sed 's/^.*GNU Awk //; s/, .*$//')
END_VERSIONS
